@* Two @page directives on one component -> its `routes` property is a two-element list
   ["/about", "/info"]. Routable pages are reached at runtime by the Router (via routes), which is
   why there is no RENDERS edge INTO a page — only page -> child-component RENDERS edges exist. *@

<h1>About EdgeHop</h1>

<p class="lead">
    EdgeHop builds a queryable graph of a .NET + JavaScript solution from Roslyn’s semantic model
    and a native oxc parse of the JS/TS, then serves it to Claude Code over an MCP server so it can
    answer structural questions without grepping. This very app is the sample it indexes. (This page
    is itself served by a component with two routes — <code>/about</code> and <code>/info</code> — so
    its node carries both templates.)
</p>

